#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:63
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kbounce; is a single player arcade game with the elements of puzzle."
msgstr ""
"&kbounce; é un xogo de arcada para un único xogador cos elementos dun "
"quebracabezas."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:67
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is played on a field, surrounded by walls, with two or more balls that "
"move about in the field bouncing off of walls. The player can build new "
"walls, decreasing the size of the active field."
msgstr ""
"Xógase nun campo rodeado por un muro, con dúas ou máis bólas a movérense e a "
"rebotaren nas paredes. O xogador pode crear paredes novas, diminuíndo o "
"tamaño do campo activo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The goal of the game is to fill at least 75&percnt; of the field and advance "
"to the next level."
msgstr ""
"O obxectivo do xogo é encher polo menos 75&percnt; do campo e avanzar ata o "
"nivel seguinte."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:77
#, no-c-format
msgid "How To Play"
msgstr "Como xogar"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:79
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The player is presented a rectangular tiled field surrounded by walls. Two "
"or more balls move about in the field and bounce off of the walls. The "
"object of the game is to limit the size of room for the balls."
msgstr ""
"Ao xogador preséntaselle un campo rectangular rodeado por unha parede. Dúas "
"ou máis bólas aparecen no campo e rebotan nas paredes. O obxectivo do xogo é "
"limitar o tamaño do espazo onde as bólas se encontran."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:83
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The size of the active area of the field is decreased by making new walls "
"that enclose areas without balls in them. To complete a level, the player "
"must decrease the size of the active field by at least 75&percnt; within the "
"time allowed."
msgstr ""
"O tamaño da área activa do campo redúcese erguendo para iso paredes novas "
"que rodeen as áreas sen bólas nelas. Para completar un nivel, o xogador ten "
"de reducir o tamañoo do campo activo en polo menos 75&percnt; dentro do "
"tempo permitido."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:87
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "New walls are built by clicking the &LMB; in an active area of the field, "
#| "at which point two walls will begin to grow in opposite directions from "
#| "the square the mouse was clicked in. Only one wall in each direction may "
#| "be growing on the screen at any given time."
msgid ""
"New walls are built by clicking the &LMB; in an active area of the field, at "
"which point one wall will begin to grow in opposite directions from the "
"square the mouse was clicked in. Only one wall in each direction may be "
"growing on the screen at any given time."
msgstr ""
"As paredes novas créanse premendo co &LMB; nunha zona activa do campo, "
"momento a partir da cal comezan a crecer dúas paredes en direccións opostas "
"desde o cadrado desde o que se premeu o rato. Só poden crecer dúas paredes "
"de cada vez na pantalla."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:91
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When the mouse is on the field, the cursor is shown as a pair of arrows "
"pointing in opposite directions, either horizontally or vertically. The "
"arrows point in the direction the walls will grow when the &LMB; is clicked. "
"This direction can be changed by clicking the &RMB;."
msgstr ""
"Cando o rato se encontra no campo, o cursor aparece como un par de frechas a "
"apuntar en direccións opostas, quere na horizontal quere na vertical. As "
"frechas apuntan para a dirección en que as paredes crecen cando for premido "
"o &LMB;. Esta dirección pode cambiarse premendo co &RMB;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:95
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A new wall has a <quote>head</quote> which moves away from the point where "
"the mouse was clicked. A wall is not permanent until this <quote>head</"
"quote> runs into another wall. If a ball collides with any part of the wall "
"except the head, before the head has run into another wall, the new wall "
"will disappear completely and one life will be lost. If a ball collides with "
"the head in the direction of the wall's growth, the wall will stop growing "
"there, and become permanent, with no loss of life. If a ball collides with "
"the head from any other side, the ball will bounce off and the wall will "
"continue to grow normally."
msgstr ""
"Unha parede nova ten unha <quote>cabeza</quote> que se move a partir do "
"punto en que o botón do rato se premeu. A parede non é permanente ata que "
"esa <quote>cabeza</quote> chegue ata outra parede. Se unha bóla bater contra "
"calquera parte da parede excepto a cabeza antes desta acadar outra parede, a "
"nova parede desaparece por completo e pérdese unha vida. Se unha bóla bater "
"na cabeza na dirección de crecemento da parede, a parede para de crecer e "
"queda permanente sen que se perda ningunha vida. Se unha bóla colidir coa "
"cabeza por outro lado calquera, a bóla rebota e a parede continuará a crecer "
"normalmente."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:100
#, no-c-format
msgid "Game Rules, Strategies and Tips"
msgstr "Regras do xogo, estratexias e suxestións"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:102
#, no-c-format
msgid "Game Rules"
msgstr "Regras do xogo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:104
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The game starts with level 1 in which two balls move around in the field. "
"The player has two lives and 90 seconds to successfully complete the level."
msgstr ""
"O xogo comeza no nivel 1, no que dúas bólas percorren todo o campo. O "
"xogador ten dúas vidas e 90 segundos para terminar o nivel."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:110
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In n-th level there are n + 1 balls. The player is given n + 1 lives. They "
"have 30 * ( n + 2 ) seconds to complete it."
msgstr ""
"No enésimo nivel, existen (n + 1) bólas. O xogador recibe (n + 1) vidas. "
"Terá tamén 30 * ( n + 2 ) segundos para o terminar."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:115
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When a ball collides with a growing wall the player looses one life. An "
"exception is the collision with wall's <quote>head</quote> when no life is "
"lost."
msgstr ""
"Cando unha bóla colide cunha parede en crecemento, o xogador perde unha "
"vida. Existe a excepción cando a colisión é coa <quote>cabeza</quote> da "
"parede porque non se perden vidas."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:121
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The goal of each level is to cover at least 75&percnt; of the field with "
"wall."
msgstr ""
"O obxectivo de cada nivel é cubrir polo menos 75&percnt; do campo cunha "
"parede."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:126
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The loss of all lives and exceeding the time allowed result in the end of "
"the game."
msgstr ""
"A perda de todas as vidas e a remate do tempo límite resultan no fin do xogo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:131
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If a player completes a level he receives 15 points for each life left, and "
"a bonus depending on the number of balls and the number of tiles filled "
"above 75&percnt;. They also advance to the next level."
msgstr ""
"Se un xogador terminar un nivel, recibe 15 puntos por cada vida restante e o "
"premio depende do número de bólas e do número de pezas enchidas por enriba "
"do 75&percnt;. Tamén avanza para o nivel seguinte."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid "Strategies and Tips"
msgstr "Estratexias e suxestións"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:144
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Many players find the game becomes quite difficult by only the third or "
"fourth level, given the number of balls on the field at once."
msgstr ""
"Moitos xogadores atopan que o xogo só se torna moito difícil a partir do "
"terceiro ou cuarto niveis, dado o número de bólas no campo dunha vez."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:152
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The trick playing &kbounce; successfully is to build <quote>corridors</"
"quote>. To build a corridor, start a pair of walls growing close to another "
"wall, and time it so that one of the walls will be hit by a ball and one of "
"the walls will not, and thus become permanent."
msgstr ""
"O truque para xogar &kbounce; é construír <quote>corredores</quote>. Para "
"crear un corredor, comece un par de paredes próximas a outra parede e "
"temporícea de modo que unha bóla acade unha das paredes pero outra non, "
"quedando deste modo permanente."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:161
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Building a corridor</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Creación dun corredor</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:167
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Building a corridor</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Creación dun corredor</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:172
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This will leave a narrow corridor only a few squares high on the field, "
"surrounded on three sides by walls. Wait for the balls to bounce into the "
"open end of the corridor, and close the corridor behind the ball with a new "
"wall. Although you will most likely lose a life for each corridor created, "
"you can trap several balls in a single corridor."
msgstr ""
"Isto deixa un corredor estreito con só algúns poucos cadrados de altura no "
"campo, rodeados en tres lados por paredes. Espere a que as bólas batan no "
"extremo aberto do corredor e peche o corredor por atrás da bóla cunha parede "
"nova. Aínda que posibelmente perdas unha vida por cada corredor creado, así "
"podes atrapar varias bólas nun único corredor."

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:182
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Capturing balls in a corridor</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>A capturar as bólas nun corredor</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:188
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Capturing balls in a corridor</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>A capturar as bólas nun corredor</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:195
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A final tip &mdash; take your time! There is plenty of time, as shown in the "
"<guilabel>Time</guilabel> display at the bottom of the screen. Rushing will "
"just get you in trouble!"
msgstr ""
"Unha suxestión final &mdash; demora o tempo que quixeres! Tes bastante "
"tempo, tal como é indicado no campo de <guilabel>Tempo</guilabel> á dereita "
"da pantalla. Se te apresas poderás ter problemas!"

